                [ void:class futuram:magnetAlloysNdFeB ] ;
            void:property futuram:refersTo ;
            rdfs:comment "The constituent (product/component/material/element individual) a PartRelation is about — the CHILD of the composition, a shared and recursively-decomposable individual. Revives the legacy futuram:refersTo (sub-property of emmo:refersTo, 300 uses in the legacy data). Replaces the rewrite's statementPart. CEON has no Constituent->resource pointer, so emmo:refersTo fills the gap." ],
        [ rdfs:label "has quantity"@en ;
            void:classPartition [ void:class ceonq:QuantityInterval ] ;
            void:property futuram:hasQuantity ;
            rdfs:comment "The amount of the constituent, as a CEON QuantityInterval (a required best estimate via futuram:hasBestValue, plus optional included min/max endpoints, each a qudt:QuantityValue). The min/max bounds, when present, carry the SPREAD of the value. On a CompositionStatement it is the measured amount; on a ClassCompositionStatement it is the aggregated amount (best value = central percentile, endpoints = the Monte-Carlo distribution's percentile bounds)." ],
        [ rdfs:label "has production"@en ;
            void:classPartition [ void:class <http://w3id.org/CEON/ontology/processODP/Process> ],
                [ void:class <http://w3id.org/CEON/ontology/process/ManufacturingProcess> ] ;
            void:property futuram:hasProduction ;
            rdfs:comment "The transformation process by which the constituent this composition statement refers to was created / produced — e.g. a CEON ManufacturingProcess, ProductionProcess or AssemblingProcess (casting, moulding, sewing, welding, assembly). Optional, so statements where it does not apply may omit it." ] ;
    rdfs:comment "A qualified relation between a CompositionStatement (about a whole) and ONE of its constituents. Carries the measured amount (ceon:hasQuantityInterval) and per-edge metadata (contentHash, quality) for that single part, and points at the shared part individual via futuram:refersTo. Deliberately NOT a ceon:Constituent: CEON's Constituent is a non-recursive leaf (not a PhysicalObject, cannot itself have constituents), whereas the part a PartRelation refers to is a full PhysicalObject that is a whole elsewhere in the recursive composition tree. The qualified relation lets the same shared part carry per-edge data without being collapsed into the edge." .

[] void:class <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_88184> ;
    void:propertyPartition [ void-ext:datatypePartition [ void-ext:datatype xsd:string ] ;
            void:property rdfs:label ] .

[] void:class futuram:V0301030105 ;
    void:propertyPartition [ rdfs:label "item mass"@en ;
            void:classPartition [ void:class qudt:QuantityValue ] ;
            void:property futuram:itemMass ;
            rdfs:comment "The absolute mass of ONE item of a Product/Component, as a QUDT quantity value in kilograms. The REFERENCE ANCHOR that turns the otherwise purely fractional (kg/kg) composition into absolute amounts: the absolute mass of a constituent in a whole = itemMass(whole) x its kg/kg composition fraction. Composition math itself stays kg/kg and is unaffected; itemMass plays no part in mass conservation. Carried per INSTANCE as a measured fact; the CLASS-level value is DERIVED, resolving exactly like a composition statement — a measured instance value wins, otherwise the class's futuram:hasAggregationStrategy derives it via the strategy's futuram:massAggregation facet (mean over slices/subclasses, or sum over composition parts). Restricted to Product/Component (countable items); Material and Element have no item mass because matter is bulk, measured per kilogram, never counted." ],
        [ void-ext:datatypePartition [ void-ext:datatype xsd:string ] ;
            void:property rdfs:label ],
        [ rdfs:label "futuram-hasCompositionStatement" ;
            void:classPartition [ void:class <http://w3id.org/CEON/ontology/product/Composition> ],
                [ void:class futuram:CompositionStatement ],
                [ void:class ceonst:ProductCompositionStatement ] ;
            void:property futuram:hasCompositionStatement ;
            rdfs:comment "Links the whole (a concrete product, component or material individual) to its per-whole CompositionStatement, which groups all of the whole's constituents as qualified part-relations. Sub-property of ceon:hasComposition (CEON's whole->composition link); revives the legacy futuram:hasCompositionStatement direction. Its inverse is ceon:compositionOf (composition->whole)." ],
        [ rdfs:label "reference year"@en ;
            void-ext:datatypePartition [ void-ext:datatype xsd:int ] ;
            void:property futuram:referenceYear ;
            rdfs:comment "The reference / production year qualifying a product (or component) CLASS, e.g. a 2026 small-car class. The year is a property of the class an instance is typed into, not of the instance or the statement itself." ] ;
    rdfs:comment "A concrete constituent class with individuals. The property partitions are the predicates an instance of this class carries (?inst a <thisClass> ; <pred> …); a class-level number is an AGGREGATE over those instances." .

