        [ rdfs:label "presented by"@en ;
            void-ext:datatypePartition [ void-ext:datatype xsd:string ] ;
            void:property futuram:presentedBy ;
            rdfs:comment "ORCID (or other identifier) of the person who presented / authored the term." ],
        [ void-ext:datatypePartition [ void-ext:datatype xsd:string ] ;
            void:property rdfs:comment ] ;
    rdfs:comment "METACLASS (punning, intentional): its members are the level-root classes whose concrete subclasses must be TIME SLICES (futuram:referenceYear xor futuram:hasReferencePeriod) to carry composition amounts. Asserted on futuram:Product and futuram:Component ONLY; futuram:Material and futuram:Element are time-independent and deliberately not members. SHACL reads this membership instead of hard-coding the two families. Deliberately a CLASS MEMBERSHIP, not a boolean annotation: a bare boolean literal in the data path triggers owlrl's literal-identity collision (Python True == 1.0 merges 'true' with quantity values of exactly 1.0 during RDFS closure)." .

